  "prompt": "How do I calculate cement aggregate and sand in KG by knowing the ratio, say 1:2:4?",
  "response": "To calculate the quantities of cement, aggregate, and sand in kilograms using a given ratio (like 1:2:4), follow these steps:\n\n1. Determine the total parts in the ratio\n   In 1:2:4, the total parts are: 1 + 2 + 4 = 7 parts\n\n2. Decide the total volume or weight you want to create\n\n3. Calculate the weight of each component:\n   - Cement (1 part): (1/7) \u00d7 Total weight\n   - Sand (2 parts): (2/7) \u00d7 Total weight\n   - Aggregate (4 parts): (4/7) \u00d7 Total weight\n\nExample:\nLet's say you want to create 70 kg of concrete mix\n\n- Cement: (1/7) \u00d7 70 = 10 kg\n- Sand: (2/7) \u00d7 70 = 20 kg\n- Aggregate: (4/7) \u00d7 70 = 40 kg\n\nVerification:\n10 + 20 + 40 = 70 kg\n1 : 2 : 4 ratio maintained\n\nNote: Actual weights may vary slightly based on material density and specific mix design.",
